{"questionId":"22516008","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A turtle walks south along the edge of the path.</p>\n<p>At time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds, the turtle’s distance, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> metres south of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>, can be modelled by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>18</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>At <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, state how far south the turtle is from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>18</mn></math> (m)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22516008","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.11f","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"At t=0, state how far south the turtle is from A.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}